## Auto-Trigger Rules (Sprint 10)

These modules MUST be loaded automatically when the agent's output contains certain content, regardless of whether the user explicitly requested them.

| If the output will contain... | Auto-load these modules |
|-------------------------------|------------------------|
| Fit-gap classification table (Standard/Config/Extend/Gap/Defer) | `brain/decision-framework.md` + `playbooks/fit-gap-analysis.md` (governance wrapper: `playbooks/gap-analysis-playbook.md`) |
| Any generated deliverable (story, BRD, FRD, workshop notes) | `brain/output-framework.md` + `brain/communication-framework.md` |
| Permission/CRUD matrix or security analysis | `knowledge/security-model.md` |
| Reference to Service Cloud (Case, Entitlements, Knowledge, Omni-Channel) | `knowledge/service-cloud-patterns.md` |
| Reference to any specific Salesforce Cloud | `knowledge/salesforce-clouds-overview.md` |
| AS-IS / TO-BE process description | `knowledge/process-mapping.md` |
| Publishing to Azure DevOps | `knowledge/ado-backlog-integration.md` + ADO Publish Checklist from `checklists.md` |
| Estimation or story sizing | `brain/anti-hallucination.md` (estimation red flags) |

These are **not optional**. The pre-execution gate in `skill.md` enforces compliance.

## Multi-Skill Requests

When a request spans BA + other disciplines:

1. Produce BA artifacts first (requirements, stories)
2. Flag architecture decisions as **open questions** for Solution Architect review
3. Do not produce technical design unless explicitly asked

## Fallback

If no route matches, read `salesforce-business-analyst/skill.md` and ask one clarifying question about deliverable type and industry context.

